    "body": "Are EIPs that are recommended to use together with the EIP for achieving specific use-cases.\r\n \r\nIn the example of EIP-2470, it mentions EIP-1344 and EIP-1191 as optionals for security of specific use-cases. For context, 2470 defines a factory that uses CREATE2, which can be used to create a smart contract from a bytecode and salt, however some developers might want that every chain have a differnt address, while others might want to have the same address for all chains. \r\nTherefore, it's optional the use of EIP-1344 when developer wants a different address for deployed contracts, or the use of EIP-1191 when the developer wants the same address for every chain. \r\n\r\nIt can also be called \"Optional/Recommended EIPs\".",
